    {
      "id": "869251982937138",
      "score": 3,
      "review_title": "Cute but terrible framerate",
      "review_description": "The idea is cute, i like the art and thank goodness it wasn’t made with AI.\n\nBut the framerate is way way way too inconsistent for such simple visuals, constantly repeating models and textures yet the framerate drops randomly even when standing still, lots of Z axis clipping too.\n\nClimbing isnt really the most natural motion, mix it with the inconsistent framerate and you get a very dizzing experience, i hope they fix that way before they decide to add more content as most people (like me) have to quit due to wanting to puke every few minutes.\n\nAlso textures really dont have to be such low quality, that’s not that relevant to framerate as thats dependant on vram and as long as it’s below what’s capable it doesnt affect perforrmance at all, which on the Quest 3 is being very unused. :)",
      "date": 1760487184,
      "review_helpful_count": 2,
      "author_display_name": "XXLaurel",
      "author_alias": "XXLaurel",
      "developer_response": {
        "body": "We'll look into this feedback, thank you Laurel! And please feel free to email me anytime at tim@mindway.studio :)",
        "date": 1760616445
      }
    },
